      <p>Figure <xref rid="Fig5" ref-type="fig">5</xref> shows the results of the likelihood ratio test for <italic>Δ</italic>HEB on this simulated data set. The results are similar to those for HEB, with the test for <italic>Δ</italic>HEB being slightly less sensitive than the test for HEB. For <italic>Δ</italic>HEB, a 4-fold change in bias is detected more than 95% of the time when <italic>N</italic>≥6. As with the test for HEB, the ability to detect smaller changes increases significantly with the number of replicates.
