				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\hat {\mathcal {L}}_{0}$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M172"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="script">ℒ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2019_2709_Article_IEq57.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> and <inline-formula id="IEq58"><alternatives><tex-math id="M173">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\hat {\mathcal {L}}_{1}$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M174"><mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="script">ℒ</mml:mi></mml:mrow><mml:mo>^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2019_2709_Article_IEq58.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> were obtained using the built-in MATLAB command fsolve applied to Eqs. <xref rid="Equ9" ref-type="">7</xref>–<xref rid="Equ11" ref-type="">9</xref> and <xref rid="Equ16" ref-type="">14</xref>–<xref rid="Equ18" ref-type="">16</xref>. In both cases, the numerical procedure was facilitated by changing variables from (<italic>λ</italic>,<italic>ω</italic>) to (<italic>v</italic>,<italic>y</italic>) through 
<disp-formula id="Equi"><alternatives><tex-math id="M175">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
