    <p>that is, <italic>λ</italic><sup><italic>a</italic></sup>=<italic>λ</italic>=<italic>e</italic><sup><italic>v</italic>−<italic>y</italic></sup> and <italic>λ</italic><sup><italic>b</italic></sup>=<italic>ω</italic><italic>λ</italic>=<italic>e</italic><sup><italic>v</italic>+<italic>y</italic></sup>. The transformed partial derivatives used to maximize the log-likelihood <inline-formula id="IEq59"><alternatives><tex-math id="M179">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
